    <joint name="StepperA_joint" type="continuous">
        <origin xyz="0.18 0.18 0.02" rpy="0 0 0" />
        <parent link="Plate" />
        <child link="StepperA" />
        <axis xyz="0 0 1" />
    </joint>
    <joint name="StepperB_joint" type="continuous">
        <origin xyz="-0.18 0.18 0.02" rpy="0 0 0" />
        <parent link="Plate" />
        <child link="StepperB" />
        <axis xyz="0 0 1" />
    </joint>
    <!--
      Motor mixing definition for controller code:
        k = 0.03839 / (2*pi)  [m/rad]  (38.39 mm travel per motor revolution)
        x_trolley = -0.5 * k * (thetaA + thetaB)  -> Slide_Slider-8
        y_slide   = -0.5 * k * (thetaA - thetaB)  -> Plate_Slider-7

      This gives:
        - A cw, B ccw (equal magnitude): pure -Y slide motion
        - A cw, B cw  (equal magnitude): pure -X trolley motion
      URDF cannot natively enforce this 2-motor coupling; apply in your control layer.
    -->
</robot>